A new point file exists that is calculated as the centroid of the polygon.</othercit>      </citeinfo>     </srccite>    </srcinfo>    <procstep>     <procdesc>This historic cemetery polygon shape file layer is based on a previous Iowa DNR point file. I have verified cemetery locations and attempted to capture actual cemetery boundaries. Polygons were digitized on the 7.5 min. USGS Quad Map Mozaic background map located on the Iowa State University GIS server. I have located and added additional cemeteries that had been missed or overlooked. I also referenced several of the aerial photography layers available on the ISU GIS server to cross check cemetery locations. Last but not least I also cross referenced to the Iowa State Historical Inventory Records here at the State Historic Preservation Office.</procdesc>     <proccont>      <cntinfo>       <cntperp>        <cntper>Don Hirt</cntper>       </cntperp>      </cntinfo>     </proccont>    </procstep>    <srcinfo>     <srccite>      <citeinfo>       <title>7.5 min.
